{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Review input is scoped to changed lines only, not full modified files.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Escalation quote: \"scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content\" implies a module handoff between diff extraction and review-input construction. MOCK-MISS: this failure appears when diff parser output is wired into prompt/input builder. REAL-INFRA/LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP are not required because the scoping bug is catchable with in-process fixtures. Rejected higher level: no behavior text requires real HTTP/OS or real model judgment.","test_description":"Wire real diff-parsing module output into the review-input builder using fixture PR patches; assert only added/changed hunks are present and unchanged file regions are excluded.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.45,"Integration":0.5,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to correct diff positions on the PR.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Escalation quote: \"attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request\" depends on real GitHub diff-position semantics over real HTTP. MOCK-HIDE: mocked API can accept invalid position mappings that GitHub would reject or render incorrectly. Rejected higher levels: no behavior text requires model output quality or multi-agent decisions.","test_description":"Against a real test PR, post inline comments using computed path/line/side/commit data, then fetch review comments from GitHub and verify they appear on intended diff hunks/lines.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Agent finds at least one real defect in a PR containing a known bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Escalation quote: \"identifies at least